summary: Hey! Do you have a Elia fic rec list?!
question: Hey! Do you have a Elia fic rec list?!
answer:
• In the Chaos of a World (series)- Robert saves Elia’s life before the Mountain could kill her and Aegon. They marry. WIP.
  • She Walks Among Vipers - a fix-it that has a happy ending
  • The Princesses in the Tower -  “King’s Landing swallows Dornish princesses and chokes on their bones.”
  • Sun and Fire, Dragon and Spear - a look at Elia’s life until the Sack
  • When the West Wind Moves - “Five people who loved Elia Martell in secret, and one who told her.” What I loved most about this story is that people fall in love with Elia which doesn’t happen in other Elia fics unless there’s an Elia ship. The idea that she’s desirable is so alien to this fandom that I constantly reread this fic.
  • Dornish to the Bone - an Elia lives fic that’s very well written (though I don’t agree with some characterizations).
  • Jenny’s Song - a unique fic that looks at the events leading up to Robert’s Rebellion. I’ve never seen Elia written like this. She’s human in an understandably ugly way.
  • Sunlight so Evanescent - looks at the aftermath of Harrenhal
  • Make a ladder of what folds and climb up in the air - a Gone Girl AU. WIP
  • Not a Sun - a fic about how Elia deals with her chronic illness (it’s so good I started rereading it while making this list lmao)
  • About Elia - drabbles about Elia
  • A Castle at the Edge of the World - Rhaegar is a prophet and Elia has Opinions
  • Time will tell (this bitter farewell) - the last conversation between Rhaegar and Elia with a nice twist
  • they kill us for their sport 
  • The Echo - a character study
  • Lemonade - Elia begins a state sanctioned affair
  • Best Served Regardless of Temperature - Elia survives but her children die. Heartbreaking but well written
  • Once Upon a Time in Westeros - Elia travels Westeros and meets all sorts of characters.
  • A Cold Corner Furthest From The Door - a soulmate au in which Elia has none

summary: I'm still skeptical over the fact that Bran had to remind Sansa of her wedding (to Ramsay) during their reunion in S7? Logically...
body:
I’m still skeptical over the fact that Bran had to remind Sansa of her wedding (to Ramsay) during their reunion in S7? Logically speaking, after spending years apart, surely the Stark siblings have a hell lot of things to share. Instead, Bran went:

“It was beautiful that night. Snow falling, just like now. And you were so beautiful in your white wedding dress.”

No doubt, he knew what happened to Sansa on her wedding night. He knew it was such a traumatic moment for her. But why? Why would he made it sound like as if that kind wedding was all she ever wanted? Why remind someone of it? Surely, by Bran’s body language (as he was telling her that), you can know that there is (or a few) a hidden agenda.

What do you think?

summary: Do you guys realize that if that Fandom Theory is right and Hela is actually Loki's birth mother that automatically turns him...
body:
Do you guys realize that if that Fandom Theory is right and Hela is actually Loki’s birth mother that automatically turns him into the Jon Snow of the Marvel Universe?

Odin = Ned Stark. They both lied about the true parentage of his grandson/nephew to protect him from a political scandal that could end in their deaths.

Loki = Jon Snow. Thought all his life that he was the son of the man who raised him even though he was not treated equally to his brother/s. Later comes the revelation that he is actually the son of one of his “father’s” greatest enemies.

Hela = Lyanna Stark. Had a baby with someone who was on the other side of the war, which forced her to leave her child under the care of a family member when she died/was sealed away. In Lyanna’s case she did it willingly, in Hela’s… probably not.

Laufey = Rhaegar Stark. Had a baby with the daughter/sister of one of his enemies, which lead to a political conflict that caused the death of thousands and eventually his own.

It’s literally the same backstory. There are probably more paralelisms but I can’t think about any right now.
